db2EQKS=>reads an antelope database and outputs an EQKS file for use in SIMULPS.  This may be buggy.  You must check the output file for formatting errors!  Offhand, I can think of
two possible bugs.  I noticed with antelope upgrades sometimes the 'use Datascope' command doesn't work due to linking problems.  Also, some of these programs
are dependent on perl version.  The included perl script refers the program to /usr/bin/perl but this may be different on your system.  Also, the current
setup is to ignore events picked by orbassoc or UNA.  I have noted this line of code using the line '###POSSIBLE BUG'.  

????????.mod.out=>output model used in GJI 2006 DeShon et al. paper.  The output contains in P, S, and Vp/Vs.

????????.stns.out=>output station corrections corresponding to the velocity model.  I have edited this file so it may be used as a STNS file for SIMULPS
 
????????.eqks.out=>final earthquake locations and travel times for P and S-P  
